for a robe, plus 10ac. Some good bracers might be golden chitin bracers, 5/5 int/agi and 5ac. <br>
Just get some newbie jeweler int items for chicken feed pp. That should put you close to 200,<br>
some items I have are Nightshade wreath, Runescale Cloak (quest at solsek temple), Gatorscale<br>
sleeves, and that's really about it. Though get the gem inlaid gauntlets quest down because<br>
with that much money you will have 200 int in no time and will be able to go for ac and other<br>
useful stats. As for where to level it's simple until 20 just solo crocs in oasis. At lvl 20 just walk<br>
to felwithe and buy your new gate spells or get someone to port you there. After that you can<br>
get all of the regular spells you will ever need with the tox/gfay gates. At 20 I would goto lake<br>
rathe and solo the aviak guards until about lvl 25. Gate to NK, croos the bridge to SK, walk<br>
straight south to lake rathe (clear across the zone, get sow :-). When you're there invis past <br>
the gnolls and head straight/right. When you get to the island with the arena zone on it, a big<br>
hole in the wall guarded by two aviak guards in towers, zone into the arena and bind. You now<br>
have gates you only need regular gate to get you your current exp or doing stuff place. Anyway<br>
 either wait there for whoever to leave or ask to take one of the spawns, if all else fails just ask<br>
around to get the location of the single spawn, though I went for the arena spawn all the time<br>
it's the safest and the fastest. Ok, nuke nuke nuke nuke, you're at 25. Gate back to NK and <br>
goto SK (you have your North Ro portal now, you can get to freeport. Your regular gate spell is<br>
now officially gravy). You probably have gone past these on your way to the lake so goto the<br>
gnoll spires and ask around for a group, or get people shouting for groups (bare with this<br>
option, you'll need to be a group leader or find generous people to group you to get groups <br>
here unless you find someone who's playing an alt because there are a lot of stupid tank only<br>
players here who think we are useless). The middle spire is basically the best so try for there, or<br>
just make a group and try to move there as soon as it becomes vacant. Ok this should be a <br>
straight shot to lvl 31 since lvl 30 is about as high as people want to group there. Anyway at lvl<br>
29 you now have your kiting ability in Bonds of Force. You can try to solo the gnolls with it or<br>
just keep grouping (I grouped) but anyway keep this spell memed, wizards with snare is nice <br>
for any group and it will save your ass at some point (don't cast it on a mob smacking you<br>
down, root the mob, move away fast, then bof if you get caught in your own bof spell it will<br>
be a short life for you unless the mob is almost dead). Ok now you might be around 30-32, so<br>
this is important. If you are evil or just neutral, a lot of wizards are very neutral, you are set. <br>
Otherwise you will need to go to FM off from Lake of ill omen or something, I just hope you are <br>
not KoS in Overthere. Anyways, gate to n ro, goto oasis, take the barge to TD, follow the right<br>
mountain wall after the barge stops to the docks in TD then take the ship to Overthere. After <br>
the ship zones into OT, jump off when you can see a wall connected with the shore. Get in sight<br>
of anything, target and con them. If you are apprenhensive or better you are set, if not OT is<br>
still good for you but you will be subject to being killed but the wandering guards and you can't<br>
really solo well and you will probably have to move on to Dreadlands(combine) sooner. Anyway,<br>
you can get groups here easy enough by making them or just sending tells to people who's<br>
groups are &quot;looking for more&quot;. At 34, you will have a good 300+ nuke at your disposal. I <br>
suggest this, try shouting or starting a group for about 5 or 10 minutes, otherwise bind at the<br>
bank and solo some of the lower blue mobs using the guards for protection, yep you now have<br>
a newbie area about 20 times bigger than normal and 30 levels higher. If you wanna make<br>
money with porting people, take a break for like 3 minutes, ask them to meet you at the<br>
outpost or at SkyFire zone for KoS people (walk along the right wall, not a long walk). I have<br>
been doing this a while now and this is where my advice ends since I've not gotten further yet.<br>
But basically at 45 or 46 I am moving to the Dreadlands for ridge groups and I'm told that is a<br>
nice place until like the early 50's. Anyway if you are able to go in the Outpost in OT, do the <br>
sarnak warbraid quest at captain rottgrime around 22-23 times to get your faction there to<br>
amiable then talk to the undead foreman and get your new hammer that lets you gate into the<br>
shipyards there at level 50. Just another gate in your arsenal, wont hurt and the outpost is an<br>
awesome place to do ports and my god there is a bank right there. :-) Well that's it, hope it<br>
helps you level up faster so most all of us will be ready to use our new incoming spells being <br>
made now...........<br>
